too many useless secretaries

125
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:21,156
Take for example, Ms. Phoenix

126
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:25,596
Poor educational background
poor experience, poor performance

127
00:14:25,631 --> 00:14:30,091
She's useless to the company. We should...

128
00:14:55,594 --> 00:14:58,722
We should fire her immediately, right?

129
00:15:03,535 --> 00:15:06,629
No. She's so young, so much potential

130
00:15:06,672 --> 00:15:10,472
With some training
she could become a model employee

131
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:12,374
and earn our company lots of money

132
00:15:17,016 --> 00:15:17,846
Late again and you're fired

133
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:23,678
Where's that bitch Phoenix? Prepare to die

134
00:15:23,722 --> 00:15:25,087
Ms. Leung, are you looking for me?

135
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:29,553
When'd you arrive?
Weren't you in line for the elevator?

136
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:32,223
I had some typing to do, so I came at 8

137
00:15:34,199 --> 00:15:37,999
You look tired. Coffee will perk you up

138
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:39,197
I can't keep that typing waiting

139
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:48,675
The man of your destiny is someone...

140
00:15:48,714 --> 00:15:53,447
who will only see you
once it's impossible to see you

141
00:15:58,457 --> 00:15:58,946
Hello

142
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:01,316
It's your Mom

143
00:16:01,527 --> 00:16:05,122
Happy Birthday!
Remember to come home for dinner

144
00:16:05,698 --> 00:16:06,596
Have you called Dad?

145
00:16:07,099 --> 00:16:09,124
How should I know where he ran off to?

146
00:16:09,168 --> 00:16:12,069
He refuses my monthly alimony

147
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:15,465
He's probably embarrassed
to take money from a woman

148
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,099
What's the big deal?

149
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:19,838
I make a bundle in real estate
and stock every year

150
00:16:20,379 --> 00:16:22,847
And he's been unemployed for forever

151
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:24,143
Hasn't he found work in Guangzhou?

152
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:27,485
How should I know?
He doesn't even have a cell phone

153
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:28,784
Forget about him

154
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:32,484
There's plenty time to talk at dinner, OK?

155
00:16:32,524 --> 00:16:33,548
OK, bye

156
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:37,852
Why are you sitting here all by yourself?

157
00:16:39,598 --> 00:16:41,964
Today's been a strange day

158
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:44,060
How strange?

159
00:16:44,103 --> 00:16:47,072
During the meeting
I was standing by the window

160
00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:48,937
When suddenly outside
appeared a young woman

161
00:16:48,974 --> 00:16:51,704
Then... she climbed up the window
like a spider

162
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:53,211
And disappeared

163
00:16:53,979 --> 00:16:58,075
Pretty high. Must have hurt falling down

164
00:16:58,117 --> 00:17:00,881
But she didn't fall. She climbed inside

165
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:03,717
She's a secretary here, named Phoenix

166
00:17:05,824 --> 00:17:08,224
So what was it? Skirt or pants?

167
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,318
A skirt

168
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:12,228
That means no pants. Quite a sight, eh?

169
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:15,196
Stop joking. Do you believe me?

170
00:17:15,401 --> 00:17:17,596
Excuse me? What does
all these about believe you?

171
00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:19,194
What kind of friends are we?

172
00:17:19,238 --> 00:17:20,899
Kindergarten, primary,
secondary, university...

173
00:17:20,939 --> 00:17:21,997
we were classmates through it all

174
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:25,067
The girls you didn't like
I helped you seduce

175
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:26,304
The girls you did like
I seduced behind your back

176
00:17:26,345 --> 00:17:28,006
What kind of friendship is that? Huh?

177
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,743
Give me your hand...

178
00:17:32,518 --> 00:17:35,385
Friends to the End, you got it?

179
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:38,151
So you believe me?

180
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:40,215
Of course... not!

181
00:17:41,994 --> 00:17:44,519
Mr. Dragon, your new secretary is here

182
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:50,129
It's her...

183
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:52,262
You... you tell her to leave

184
00:17:52,304 --> 00:17:53,794
Tell her to leave? No way!

185
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:56,740
Beautiful and can crawl up windows?

186
00:17:56,775 --> 00:17:57,707
Tell her to get out of here!

187
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,142
If you don't want, I want

188
00:18:01,647 --> 00:18:05,447
Excuse me Ms., but I'm afraid
you're too pretty to be my secretary

189
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:06,508
Don't worry

190
00:18:06,552 --> 00:18:09,350
Tomorrow I won't wear make up
I promise to be ugly

191
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:10,946
You can call me by
my English name: Phoenix

192
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,547
If you want anything, just let me know

193
00:18:13,492 --> 00:18:15,050
Please climb a window

194
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:15,924
Excuse me?

195
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:17,895
He said you can climb windows!

196
00:18:18,464 --> 00:18:21,695
I'm a secretary, not a window cleaner

197
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:23,098
Just joking

198
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:25,729
I'm Kiddie Kim, his best friend

199
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,171
Of course Kiddie Kim is
Dragon's best friend

200
00:18:29,241 --> 00:18:32,176
Please bring us two coffees

201
00:18:32,211 --> 00:18:34,304
No problem. Anything else just instruct

202
00:18:35,681 --> 00:18:37,410
I don't care. I'll give you fifty... No...

203
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:39,747
You give me fifty thousand
I'll take her off your hands

204
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:43,380
No. I really saw her
climbing up the window

205
00:18:43,889 --> 00:18:48,417
I can only imagine... her
climbing onto the bed

206
00:18:50,162 --> 00:18:51,424
Cool down, will you?

207
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:54,023
Impossible. I can't help myself

208
00:18:54,399 --> 00:18:55,923
So pretty

209
00:18:56,902 --> 00:18:58,369
Here you go again...

210
00:18:58,403 --> 00:18:59,529
Get your mind out of the bedroom...

211
00:19:01,173 --> 00:19:06,270
Stop it...

212
00:19:07,379 --> 00:19:08,812
Do I need to step out?

213
00:19:13,018 --> 00:19:14,246
You two are busy?

214
00:19:14,286 --> 00:19:18,017
No. Dragon and I were
discussing some contractual matters

215
00:19:18,056 --> 00:19:19,956
Yes You should consider him

216
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,254
OK

217
00:19:22,127 --> 00:19:25,096
The affairs of the day call
I can't let work wait

218
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:27,223
Back to work Back to work...

219
00:19:28,133 --> 00:19:29,100
Back to work

220
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:33,298
Boss, you were looking for me?

221
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:36,739
Yes, I need you
to represent me at a dinner

222
00:19:36,775 --> 00:19:37,707
What dinner?

223
00:19:37,743 --> 00:19:39,472
Having dinner with some business friends

224
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:42,912
They want to discuss
how to boycott Boss White

225
00:19:42,948 --> 00:19:44,813
